Program: Outlook
Title: 13/07/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00hqtxn
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 14 Jul 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, we speak to David Wooding who was political editor of the paper at the centre of the UK phone hacking crisis - the News of the World. He talks about his career as a tabloid journalist, the pressure to come up with exclusive stories and what it was like to find himself on the receiving end of press attention. Show less